CONTENT:
Caltrans Struggles to hire on new surveyors, especially ones with the specialized experience needed to do things to the Caltrans standard. This problem could be solved in two ways;

1. Short term, allowing people to telework from distances normally not practical to commute from will allow recruitment for office positions that are both hard to fill and do not require an in person role. This also incentivizes private sector surveyors looking to earn their License to join Caltrans for the hard to get office hours. 

2. Long term, emphasizing recruitment in high schools and colleges through our JET and TET program will let us get people that would normally go into the private sector apprenticeships and expand the number of people considering surveys at all.

